title: Grade 7 Social Studies Mock Exam 2
subject: SocialStudies
description: Second model ECZ Grade 7 Social Studies paper. Focuses on heritage, governance, environmental issues, and map skills. Includes multiple-choice and open-ended questions.

questions.questions: This is **Grade 7 Social Studies Mock Exam 2**. It tests your knowledge on Zambia’s history, government, environment, and maps. Some questions require short written answers, others are multiple choice. Answer all questions.

**SECTION A: HERITAGE AND HISTORY**
Answer these questions about Zambia’s early people and independence.
Which of these was a result of **colonial rule** in Zambia?
questions.explanation: Colonial rule brought forced labour and taxation of local people.

questions.questions: Why was the **Federation of Rhodesia and Nyasaland** opposed by many Zambians?
options: It gave more power to Africans
It favoured white settlers and denied African rights
questions.explanation: The federation mostly benefited white settlers and limited African political rights.

questions.questions: Name one political party that fought for Zambia's independence.
questions.explanation: UNIP, led by Dr. Kenneth Kaunda, played a major role in Zambia’s independence.

questions.questions:
**SECTION B: GOVERNANCE AND CIVIC LIFE**
Answer questions about your rights, responsibilities, and leadership.
What is a **constitution**?
options: The laws that govern a country
questions.explanation: A constitution is the supreme law of the land.

questions.questions: Which of these is a **right** every Zambian child has?
options: The right to own a company
The right to vote at age 10
questions.explanation: Every child has the right to education, as protected by the constitution.

questions.questions: List one way citizens can participate in national governance.
questions.explanation: Voting is a key way citizens influence governance.

questions.questions: Who is responsible for passing laws in Zambia?

**SECTION C: ENVIRONMENT AND SUSTAINABLE DEVELOPMENT**
Answer questions related to the use and protection of natural resources.
What is the **main cause of soil erosion** in farming areas?
questions.explanation: Clearing vegetation and overgrazing leaves soil exposed to erosion.

questions.questions: What activity is described in this sentence: 'a group of workers wearing helmets using tools to dig underground rocks'
questions.explanation: The image shows a mining activity.

questions.questions: Give one method of conserving water in homes.
questions.answer: By closing taps when not in use.

questions.questions: Which of the following is a **renewable resource**?
questions.explanation: Solar energy can be replenished and does not run out like minerals.

questions.questions:
**SECTION D: MAP READING AND INTERPRETATION**
Use the symbols and directions to answer the following questions.
What does this symbol represent on a map?
questions.explanation: A cross symbol often represents a hospital.

questions.questions: Why is it important to use **map keys**?
questions.explanation: Map keys help interpret symbols used on a map.

questions.questions: Which province in Zambia is **Kariba Dam** located in?
questions.explanation: Kariba Dam is located in Southern Province along the Zambezi River.

questions.questions: Name the closest neighbouring country to Zambia that is directly east of it
questions.explanation: This tests learners' map drawing and spatial awareness skills.
